Although the vast majority of wanderers report entering the Backrooms in '''[[Level 0]]''', and occasionally '''[[Level 1]]''', there are various accounts of '''Level 2''' being initially entered by wanderers. At present, it is the furthest-known level directly accessible from baseline reality.
{{Blurimage|file=Spoopy level2.png|caption=<span style="color: white">An image of '''Level 2'''.</span>|width=600px|align=center}}<br>
{{Blurimage|file=Level2main.png|caption=<span style="color: white">A new section of '''Level 2'''.</span>|hovertext=Areas of Level 2 that appear during the outbursts usually have mostly fragmented walls that somewhat border them with their older variations.}}
== <span style="font-family: Warownia;">⤳ Description</span> ==
'''Level 2''' is a vast network of interconnected utility tunnels, maintenance shafts, and rusting pipes. Unlike the typically inconstant-level environments of the Backrooms, space in '''Level 2''' does not ''physically'' shift live, lending much of the level a relative ease of navigation. The level’s architecture, which can differ from place to place, remains largely uniform in its diversity and appearance across areas.

Its layout, however, reportedly becomes more complex the farther one travels from the entrance, with corridors that run up and down and may impede travel or cause injury, especially in dark areas. Fortunately, however, there have been no reports of entities lurking around these areas, most likely due to the heat and extreme humidity.

The supply of provisions and hydration is heavily limited in '''Level 2''' despite the number of water pipes in the level. Because no machinery or boiler rooms required for these pipes to function have been discovered, and because of the humid temperatures in various areas of the level, rust, bacteria, and other pathogens can overwhelm the insides of these pipes, which may contain '''[[Object 1|Almond Water]]'''.

Unknown diseases, mutated bacteria, and viruses have been discovered within these networks, meaning that the source of most epidemics in the Backrooms is usually '''Level 2'''. These pathogens typically spread through direct contact or by consuming water from pipes. These are to be avoided, whether by ingesting them or by staying away to prevent accidental exposure.

Geological activity in '''Level 2''' is prevalent, and earthquakes occur as often as in regions on the Ring of Fire in '''[[the Frontrooms]]'''. Any powerful enough tremors can demolish and therefore render parts of the level inaccessible due to the lack of maintenance work, although most do not have enough intensity to inflict severe damage on the level's structure. The circumstances behind these earthquakes presumably originate from cracks within '''Level 2'''’s giant concrete mass. Chunks of them may push against each other, and with these theorized crevices within, one of them may slip from stress buildup, thereafter releasing an outburst of energy.
{{Blurimage|file=Twistinglevel2.jpg|caption=<span style="color: white">An early image of '''Level 2'''.</span>|hovertext=The back of the photograph indicates that it was taken on 09/10/1983.}}
The level's temperature varies by location, and escaping extreme areas often proves fruitless. Those with steam pipes can reach 60–100 degrees Celsius, while areas with prevalent air vents are colder. Snow may also form in certain months, but it is not known how it can enter in the first place.<ref>The snowfall in the level can be filled with debris, but it is relatively safe to consume when boiled.</ref> Exiting the level through this method is not advised, as it is rare to find a system big enough to crawl through for hours. Chipping away the concrete is also futile, as the distance between cracks within the level’s matrix can be greater than that of tectonic plates in '''[[the Frontrooms]]''', which otherwise could be used to easily traverse through the level.

Instances of changing layouts are also common, but the anomaly has yet to be captured on video, despite many stating that they were able to touch the seemingly hallucinatory objects. Exploring '''Level 2''' while simultaneously recording would not prevent the changes from occurring, and, more often than not, the recording would show the person filming experiencing the anomaly in real time, as attested by the cameramen themselves.

Therefore, the phenomenon is generally considered a purely geometric effect of exposure to anomalies prominent at earlier levels. The only solid corroboration of the theory, a window overlooking what appears to be the Whole, seems to be taken in a vacated attic that is partly or mostly constructed out of wood. However, no location/level has matched the description other than '''Level 2''' itself. Although the level is mostly constructed of concrete, certain older areas are made of wood, though cobwebs cannot form, given that the environment is highly unsuitable for invertebrates.
{{Blurimage|file=Level 2_.png|caption=<span style="color: white">A brightly lit area of '''Level 2'''.</span>|hovertext=Most areas in Level 2 are poorly lit, with very few that are fully illuminated.}}
While there are at times signs of human activity, encounters with outside parties of wanderers have currently never been confirmed. Additionally, communication devices such as radios and walkie-talkies completely malfunction on the level. The circumstances are unknown, as linear space in '''Level 2''' does not alter drastically, nor even a slight bit, unlike '''[[Level 0]]'''. However, the possibly infinite concrete space of '''Level 2''' is theorized to be the perpetrator.

There are no doors that can be found, and recollections of similar fixtures, such as windows, trapdoors, and scuttle doors, are mostly identified as cases of paramnesia. Exits are instead found in the level's few crawlspaces, sometimes crowded by extensive, inoperative assemblages of wires, possibly punctured, which flood the claustrophobic stretch. Moreover, these wires still hold electrical charge and can often result in serious injury.

Although still speculative, there is a possibility that '''Level 2''' contains an anomaly that directly influences wanderers in the level. Recent '''Level 2''' entrants have been tested to expend more energy than the average person and to produce unnatural amounts of adrenaline when the body is active (e.g., running). Furthermore, most who enter '''Level 2''' also report either being more energetic upon arrival, but more exhausted as they exit; entities or subjects (human/animals) born in the Backrooms are not affected, however, and it seems only Earthlings experience the anomalous spasm. Escaping from entities, while easier, can increase the risk of dying from exhaustion or further attacks by entities in the long run.
